1	/**
2	 * LAYERINFINITE — lib/outcome-score-inference.ts
3	 * ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
4	 * Production-Grade 3-Layer Outcome Score Inference Engine
5	 *
6	 * Replaces the hardcoded `outcome_score ?? 0.5` fallback with a
7	 * signal-driven inference pipeline when the developer does not
8	 * provide an explicit outcome_score via score_fn.
9	 *
10	 * Architecture:
11	 *   Layer 1 — Hard Signals  (success, error_code, retry_attempt)
12	 *   Layer 2 — Soft Signals  (business_outcome, verifier, cross_event)
13	 *   Layer 3 — Relative Perf (adaptive baseline from action history)
14	 *
15	 * INVARIANTS:
16	 *   - Developer-provided score_fn always wins — inference is NEVER run
17	 *     when outcome_score is explicitly provided (score_origin='provided').
18	 *   - Inference confidence is capped at 0.85 — never as reliable as
19	 *     developer-provided scores.
20	 *   - Import rows skip inference by default; opt-in is available via
21	 *     ingest-core option enableInferenceWhenSkipTrust.
22	 *   - outcome-weighting.ts is NOT changed — inference feeds it
23	 *     automatically via the improved outcome_score values.
24	 * ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
25	 */
